<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,800,1171]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Notes.— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1894" box="[300,434,874,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[300,434,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rupestrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still is the most poorly known genus in the family. The molecular data place this genus as the sister-group next to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Turton" authorityYear="1831" box="[547,617,913,938]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Abida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,617,913,938]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Abida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kokshoorn, B." box="[682,930,913,939]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref35737" refString="Kokshoorn, B. (2008) Resolving Riddles and Presenting New Puzzles in Chondrinidae Phylogenetics. PhD thesis, Leiden University, 192 pp." type="book" year="2008">Kokshoorn 2008: 34</bibRefCitation>
). Additional morphological and molecular work is necessary but the material to enable such studies is not (yet) available, in particular not for the African taxa. Pilsbry (1918: 332–356) provisionally accepted 16 species, 5 of which are endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[1248,1316,990,1016]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Sicily</collectingRegion>
and 8 are endemic to northern Africa. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beckmann, K. - H." box="[486,697,1029,1055]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="49 - 78" refId="ref33589" refString="Beckmann, K. - H. (2002) Elemente einer Revision der endemischen Rupestrellen Siziliens. In: Falkner, M., Groh, K. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (Eds), Collectanea Malacologica, 49 - 78, Hackenheim." type="book chapter" year="2002">Beckmann (2002)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 4 species as endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[1127,1196,1029,1055]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, with 11 subspecific taxa in total.To stabilize the nomenclature of the two most widespread species, viz. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cantraine" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1130,1261,1068,1093]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="philippii">
<emphasis box="[1130,1261,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">R. philippii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Roth" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1318,1428,1068,1093]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rhodia">
<emphasis box="[1318,1428,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">R. rhodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a 
<typeStatus box="[171,278,1106,1132]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">lectotype</typeStatus>
is here selected for the former species. Additionally we present an uncritical, annotated list of currently recognized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1894" box="[362,496,1145,1170]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,496,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rupestrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa.
</paragraph>
